book_team?":false,"team_private?":false,"vulnerability_information":"Although by default, all the communication in the Secret web app happens over HTTPS, if this is changed to HTTP, the requests are still normally processed. \r\n\r\nFor example, the request to send a download link to a phone number can be as simple as\r\nPOST /_/send-download-link HTTP/1.1\r\nHost: www.secret.ly\r\n\r\n{\"PhoneNumber\":\"xxxxxxxxxx\"}\r\n\r\nThe above request is sent to the target www.secret.ly over HTTP. This is successfully processed and the phone number in question gets a link to download the application.\r\n\r\nNot to mention, an attacker can automate this and spam users sending them links to download this app even if they are not interested. There is also no controlling factor to stop the spam. This might be considered a totally different issue but I am reporting it together with this. ","vulnerability_information_html":"\u003cp\u003eAlthough by default, all the communication in the Secret web app happens over HTTPS, if this is changed to HTTP, the requests are still normally processed. \u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003eFor example, the request to send a download link to a phone number can be as simple as\u003cbr\u003e\nPOST /_/send-download-link HTTP/1.1\u003cbr\u003e\nHost: \u003ca href=\"/redirect?url=http%3A%2F%2Fwww.secret.ly\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener noreferrer\"\u003e\u003cspan\u003ewww.secret.ly\u003c/span\u003e\u003ci class=\"icon-external-link\"\u003e\u003c/i\u003e\u003c/a\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003e{\u0026quot;PhoneNumber\u0026quot;:\u0026quot;xxxxxxxxxx\u0026quot;}\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003eThe above request is sent to the target \u003ca href=\"/redirect?url=http%3A%2F%2Fwww.secret.ly\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener noreferrer\"\u003e\u003cspan\u003ewww.secret.ly\u003c/span\u003e\u003ci class=\"icon-external-link\"\u003e\u003c/i\u003e\u003c/a\u003e over HTTP. This is successfully processed and the phone number in question gets a link to download the application.\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003eNot to mention, an attacker can automate this and spam users sending them links to download this app even if they are not interested. There is also no controlling factor to stop the spam. This might be considered a totally different issue but I am reporting it together with this. \u003c/p\u003e\n","original_report_id":null,"original_report_url":null,"attachments":[],"allow_singular_disclosure_at":"2014-03-16T09:02:16.635Z","allow_singular_disclosure_after":-214255599.68369943,"singular_disclosure_allowed":true,"vote_count":3,"voters":["zelzal","spetr0x","hamzafisa"],"structured_scope":null,"abilities":{"assignable_team_members":[],"assignable_team_member_groups":[]},"can_edit_custom_fields_attributes":false,"activities":[{"id":6862,"is_internal":false,"editable":false,"type":"Activities::BugResolved","message":"This should be fixed now. Thanks!","markdown_message":"\u003cp\u003eThis should be fixed now. Thanks!\u003c/p\u003e\n","automated_response":false,"created_at":"2014-02-14T09:02:16.721Z","updated_at":"2014-02-14T09:02:16.721Z","actor":{"username":"davidbyttow","cleared":false,"url":"/davidbyttow","profile_picture_urls":{"medium":"https://profile-photos.hackerone-user-content.com/variants/000/002/652/895175be46662e28efaca47ab024f3c7f7c4a197_original.jpeg/eb31823a4cc9f6b6bb4db930ffdf512533928a68a4255fb50a83180281a60da5"},"hackerone_triager":false,"hackerone_employee":false},"reporter":{"username":"anshuman_bh","url":"/anshuman_bh"},"genius_execution_id":null,"team_handle":"secret","actor_is_team_member":true,"actor_is_concealed_member":false},{"id":6882,"is_internal":false,"editable":false,"type":"Activities::Comment","message":"Please send email with your mailing address to bounty@secret.ly if you'd like to receive swag.","markdown_message":"\u003cp\u003ePlease send email with your mailing address to \u003ca title=\"bounty@secret.ly\" href=\"mailto:bounty@secret.ly\" rel=\"nofollow noopener nore